17/12/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Presidency has agreed to nominate Croat Democratic Union leader Barisa Colak as the new prime minister-designate, according to the presidency's Croat member, Dragan Covic.
He told Mostar TV late Monday (16 December) that the respective parties will have until Wednesday to consider the nomination, followed by a vote in the BiH Parliament.
If elected, Colak would head the BiH Council of Ministers for a four-year term.
(OHR Sources - 17/12/02;
NTV Hayat, PBS BiH, HINA - 16/12/02)
